properties.areaDesc: Southern Cook/North Shore; Southern Lake/North Shore
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 2:56AM CST until January 14 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...ACCUMULATING SNOW THIS MORNING...

.A potent, but fast-moving, system will pass through the region
this morning, which will bring widespread accumulating snow and
light freezing drizzle to the Northland. The heaviest snowfall
will affect portions of the North Shore generally northeast of Two
Harbors, and portions of north-central Minnesota including
International Falls, Cook, and Ely. Some freezing drizzle may mix
in at times as the snow begins to taper off, but snow will be the
primary threat. Look for precipitation to end by late this
morning.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation with additional snow accumulation of up
to two inches and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Southern Cook and Southern Lake Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand Portage Reservation.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM CST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions this morning,
including the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM CST THIS MORNING
